<p><b> 1. Page 156 
</b></p>
<p>Paragraph 1019<b> </b><i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>1019. In a letter dated 29 December 2009, the Government of India responded to the 
communication sent on 29 July 2009 as follows. The Government has examined the 
communication and found the allegations to be inaccurate. No Government of India official 
contacted the subject in Geneva on 8 June 2009. As regards the allegation of a visit by an 
official of the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) to her house in Punjab, the allegation 
has been investigated by the local office of the CBI that has found it to be untrue. 
Subsequent to the allegation, the CBI has contacted the subject and provided her with 
contact details to help her in case any person approaches the subject at the behest of the 
CBI in future. <b> 
</b></p>
